A regular tetrahedrization constitutes the background of the mesh.
The boundary faces may be of very much smaller size.
It is possible to pass quickly or not from the boundary to the
interior with few or many layers of tetrahedra.

The real ACCRTE defines tis velocity of growing.
If L is the averaged length of the 3 edges of the boundary face,
then, approximately

L * ACCRTE will be the size of the tetrahedron edge of the first level.
L * ACCRTE * ACCRTE will be the size of the tetrahedron edge of the second level
...
and so on until this size attains ARETGR the size of the regular grid.

ACCRTE = 1.2 may be used as the default value.

ACCRTE <= 1.0 imposes in fact the value 1.2 BY DEFAULT.

ACCRTE =  2.0 leads to a small number of layers
The size varies quickly.

ATTENTION:
This choice of ACCRTE must be chosen with careful, depending of the thickness
of the object.
